preibisch_imagej.display

Interface Zoomable


  • public interface Zoomable
    Defines methods needed to adjust the zoom of an ImageCanvas.
    Author:
    Barry DeZonia, Grant Harris, Curtis Rueden

    • Method Summary

      • setZoomAtPoint

        void setZoomAtPoint(double factor,
                    RealCoords pos)
        Zooms to the given scale factor, such that the specified position in data coordinates remains at the same place in the viewport.

        This is useful for repeatedly zooming at a chosen point in the data.

        Parameters:
        factor - The new scale factor.
        pos - The data coordinates to keep in the same place within the viewport.

      • setZoomAtPoint

        Parameters:
        factor - The new scale factor.
        pos - The panel coordinates to keep in the same place within the viewport.
